<article data-uuid="9e18e1b2-53c5-30fe-8b96-546586136230" data-type="story" data-reactid="9">
<div class="canvas-body Wow(bw) Cl(start) Mb(20px) Fz(15px) Lh(1.6) C($c-fuji-grey-l) Ff($ff-secondary) D(i)" data-reactid="10">
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; color: #26282a; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" data-reactid="12">Future Farm Technologies Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221; or &#8220;Future Farm&#8221;) (CSE:FFT) (FFRMF) is pleased to announce estimated 2018 projections on its 10-acre operating greenhouse. This 10-acre greenhouse in&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Apopka, Florida</span>&#194;&#160;is located in a designated legal grow zone with close proximity to&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Orlando</span>, which has a local population of almost 2.5 million and attracts over 62 million visitors annually. The greenhouse business will provide Future Farm with cash flow while serving as a major building block for the Company as it prepares to position itself in the emerging&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Florida</span>&#194;&#160;cannabis market, estimated to climb to $1.6 billion in medical cannabis sales by 2020.</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" data-reactid="13">The Company plans to upgrade the nursery&#8217;s technology platform with new computers and software, a new phone system and fully implemented automated accounting, inventory management and order tracking systems. In addition, the Company plans to activate the online ordering platform, which to date has been non-functional, to penetrate higher margin markets such as direct to consumer wedding sales. Finally, the Company plans to initiate an online and social media marketing effort in part by employing the services of an ad agency.</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; color: #26282a; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" data-reactid="14">As of&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-chron">July 2017</span>,&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Florida</span>&#194;&#160;had approximately&#194;&#160;26,000&#194;&#160;registered medical cannabis patients, and by October the number of&#194;&#160;registered medical cannabis patients&#194;&#160;surged to 38,000. It is anticipated that these numbers will likely continue to grow significantly over the next few years, due to the large number of retirees residing in&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Florida</span>. It is expected that the&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Florida</span>&#194;&#160;cannabis market will be only second in size to&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">California</span>, which in the last quarter of 2017 had 34 percent market share of legal pot sales.&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Colorado</span>,&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Washington</span>&#194;&#160;and&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Oregon</span>&#194;&#160;had 41 percent share combined as of the same time period.</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; color: #26282a; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" data-reactid="15">&#8220;We continue to execute on our planned strategy of building a portfolio of valuable, revenue-generating assets in the fastest growing cannabis and hemp markets in the country,&#8221; says&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-person">William Gildea</span>, Future Farm&#8217;s CEO and Chairman. &#8220;Our portfolio has grown quickly over the past year with assets acquired in&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Rhode Island</span>,&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Maine</span>,&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">California</span>and&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Puerto Rico</span>, in addition to the acquisition of our&#194;&#160;<span class="xn-location">Florida</span>&#194;&#160;greenhouse and nursery.&#8221;</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" data-reactid="16">On behalf of the Board,</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; color: #26282a; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" data-reactid="17"><b>Future Farm</b>&#194;&#160;<b>Technologies Inc.</b></p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; color: #26282a; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" data-reactid="18"><span class="xn-person">William Gildea</span>, CEO &amp; Chairman</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; color: #26282a; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" data-reactid="19"><b>About Future Farm</b></p>
