<div class="auth-prov-logos D(tbc) Va(t) " data-reactid="3">Cara Therapeutics, Inc. (CARA), a biopharmaceutical company focused on developing and commercializing new chemical entities designed to alleviate pruritus and pain by selectively targeting peripheral kappa opioid receptors, today announced the dosing of the first patient &#194;&#160;in a Phase 1 safety and pharmacokinetic (PK) trial of Oral KORSUVA&#226;&#132;&#162; (CR845/difelikefalin) in patients with chronic liver disease (CLD). Data from this trial will directly inform the design for the planned Phase 2 trial of Oral KORSUVA&#226;&#132;&#162; in patients suffering from moderate-to-severe CLD-associated pruritus, a condition for which there are currently no approved therapies in the United States.</div>
