<article data-uuid="39a700b8-4253-39b0-a09c-01637874c77d" data-type="story" data-reactid="9">
<div class="canvas-body Wow(bw) Cl(start) Mb(20px) Fz(15px) Lh(1.6) C($c-fuji-grey-l) Ff($ff-secondary) D(i)" data-reactid="10">
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em;" data-reactid="12">The Indiana House recently passed&#194;&#160;Senate Bill 52&#194;&#160;by a unanimous vote of 93-0. SB-52 legalizes hemp-derived CBD oil with no more than 0.3 percent THC. Similar legislation,&#194;&#160;House Bill 1214, recently passed the Senate Corrections and Criminal Law Committee by a 6-2 vote. Differences between the bills will need to be resolved before it heads to the governor&#226;&#128;&#153;s desk for his signature. In addition, the state&#226;&#128;&#153;s&#194;&#160;House Bill 1137&#194;&#160;would establish an industrial hemp pilot program.</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" data-reactid="13">&#226;&#128;&#156;We support Indiana&#226;&#128;&#153;s latest legislative actions that bring the state one step closer to legalizing hemp-derived CBD oil and creating an infrastructure for a viable hemp program that can create jobs and spur economic activity,&#226;&#128;&#157; said Hemp, Inc. CEO Bruce Perlowin.</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em;" data-reactid="14">Hemp, Inc.&#194;&#160;announced&#194;&#160;in October, 2017, that the Company and its strategic farming partners were on the forefront of North Carolina&#226;&#128;&#153;s first hemp harvest. In August, 2017, Hemp, Inc.&#194;&#160;announced&#194;&#160;the official launch of its NuAxon Tech CO2 Supercritical Extractor, purchased from NuAxon BioScience. Hemp, Inc. uses this device to process raw hemp into CBD extracts and oil as part of its strategic business model.</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em;" data-reactid="15">&#226;&#128;&#156;As North Carolina becomes the hemp epicenter of the United States, with Hemp, Inc. planning to grow as much as 25,000 acres next year &#226;&#128;&#147; more than the entire country combined&#194;&#160;in 2017&#194;&#160;&#226;&#128;&#147; we are deeply encouraging of states that are taking action to clarify hemp-derived CBD oil&#226;&#128;&#153;s legal status while also creating an infrastructure for a hemp program that can lead to a resurgence of the family farm,&#226;&#128;&#157; stated&#194;&#160;Perlowin.</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em;" data-reactid="16">Previously, Hemp, Inc.&#194;&#160;announced&#194;&#160;its support of the Alaska House of Representatives&#226;&#128;&#153; unanimous passage of a bill to legalize industrial hemp and establish a pilot program.</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" data-reactid="17">ABOUT HEMP, INC.</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" data-reactid="18">With a deep-rooted social and environmental mission at its core, Hemp, Inc. seeks to build a business constituency for the American small farmer, the American veteran, and other groups experiencing the ever-increasing disparity between tapering income and soaring expenses. As a leader in the industrial hemp industry with ownership of the largest commercial multi-purpose industrial hemp processing facility in North America, Hemp, Inc. believes there can be tangible benefits reaped from adhering to a corporate social responsibility plan.</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" data-reactid="19">SOCIAL NETWORKS:</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em;" data-reactid="20">https://www.twitter.com/hempinc&#194;&#160;(Twitter)</p>
